The ultimate multiplayer filler game - it's quick, compact (I own the travel edition which I consider to be THE BEST version of For Sale) and super easy to teach, but at the same time it offers just the right number of meaningful decisions. The artwork is great and really enhances the theme of the game. A lovely package, I will play For Sale anywhere, anytime and with anyone.

/update, March 2019: 35 plays in and I can't get tired of it. This game has never let me down and has proven to be a fantastic party game countless times. I couldn't ask for a better filler, it's a stellar game in its category.

//update: I've had so much success with this game over the years (I've played it 80 times). This is the best filler game of all time.
